Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
report_disk(25.10)                                          report_disk(25.10)

Name
       report_disk - Reports the disk metrics of the current working directory
       and the /tmp directory

Syntax
       report_disk

       [-help]

       [-dir <directory_name>]

       Reports  the disk metrics of the current working directory and the /tmp
       directory. The output of this command allows you to investigate  Mb/sec
       throughput of the disk and disk I/O requirements.

       This  command  also reports the used and free disk space for the direc-
       tory specified by the -dir parameter (default is /tmp).

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each report_disk parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man report_disk.

       -dir <directory_name>
              Specifies  the name of the directory in which disk metric infor-
              mation is written. The default directory is /tmp.

Examples
              * The following is a sample output for report_disk:

                >report_disk

                DISK_INFO : 206.66 Mb/S   381G total   1.1G used    359G  free
                /env(TMPDIR)

                {206.66 381G 1.1G 359G}

              * The following command shows the usage of report_disk -dir:

                >report_disk -dir .

                DISK_INFO  :  98.51  Mb/S   9.6T total   9.3T used   395G free
                .

                {98.51 9.6T 9.3T 395G}

